The paper deals with security issues in cooperative spectrum sensing, which involves the use of machine learning to construct a surrogate model of the fusion center's decision model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a generic algorithm to create malicious sensing data, which could fall under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of influence-limiting policy to defend against attacks, which could be related to the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with the overall disruption ratio reduction, which could be related to the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
